    {
      "id": 13, "type": "Note", "pos": [40, -250], "size": [900, 200], "flags": {}, "order": 12, "mode": 0,
      "properties": { "text": "" },
      "widgets_values": ["PER-ELEMENT PALETTES -> COMPOSITIONAL DECONSTRUCTION\n\nEach region of one generation gets its own reference palette and its own placement.\n\n1) Two reference images each yield a <=5 color element palette (Ideogram Element Palette).\n2) Each palette feeds an Ideogram Element Builder as color_palette, paired with a bounding box ([ymin, xmin, ymax, xmax], 0-1000) and a description. A third builder adds a text overlay element (type 'text', no palette).\n3) Ideogram Element Collector gathers the three element JSON strings into one compositional_deconstruction block, and reports overlapping TEXT boxes (none here -- add a second overlapping text element to see the warning).\n\nThe compositional_deconstruction block is ready to drop into a full Ideogram 4 prompt. ShowText nodes are optional (ComfyUI-Custom-Scripts)."],
      "color": "#432", "bgcolor": "#653", "title": "README"
    }
